{
  "texts": [
    "Image watermarking methods embed invisible signals either during training or sampling phase.",
    "[22] proposes a method to watermark pre-trained GANs without access to training data.",
    "[32] exploits DDIM invertibility to embed structural patterns into the frequency domain of the initial noise vector during sampling, achieving an effective and invisible image watermarking.",
    "[37] implements a performance-preserving watermarking for diffusion models by incorporating diffused bit information into Gaussian noise in the latent space.",
    "[46] has explored generalizing image watermarking techniques to structural tabular data."
  ]
}